parameters:
The one-armed Opro, seeing numerous skilled warriors who
were invited by King Lex to join the Imperial Army but
declined, thinks that the old soldiers are unnecessary.

One-armed Opro: You guys are the leading skilled warriors.
I'm proud to have fought alongside you in that place.

\CL The Aftermath of the One-Armed OproOpro, who had made
the ancient ruins their base and continued to protect the
creatures living here, reluctantly went monster hunting when
asked for help with procuring food.

\CL The visual of the one-armed swordsman has captivated
many artists. Paintings and stories depicting their life
become the dreams of young boys.

\CL The number of works surpassed the guild master Pruce,
whom Opro admired.

\CL The Aftermath of the Mysterious Creature?The creature,
which seems to possess considerable intelligence, appears to
be quite fond of Opro and calls them Opro.

\CL After Opro's death in the ancient ruins, a grave for
Opro was created next to the tomb of the first guild master,
Pruce.

\CL It is said that Opro, who protected the symbol of the
great sword for a long time.

Clea: Before fighting the ogres... my life was just running
away, if we hadn't met in the forest at night.

One-armed Opro: If I hadn't met you, I wouldn't have been
able to come here and keep my promise to my friends.

One-armed Opro: Life is a combination of chance and
inevitability, but it was your own courage that made you
decide to fight.

Mage Relm: A greatsword imbued with magic power... Hmm, how
can I do it without a crystal...

One-armed Opro: Isn't it the job of your magic academy to
unravel and put into practical use things like this?

Mage Relm: Of course! Leave it to me! I have plenty of
collaborators outside of the academy, you know!

Thief Nora: Thanks to Opro-san, I was able to come here and
now I know where I came from!

One-armed Opro: You might be the strongest, even though
you've lost your memories and your hometown, you're still
living in a foreign land.

Thief Nora: Because you all helped me! The captain, Clea-
san and the others, and also Opro-san!

Priestess Sophia: As a priestess, I intend to live by
atoning for various things from the past.

One-armed Opro: The shadows will always chase after you, but
don't forget that there is a warm sunny spot around you.

Priestess Sophia: Sometimes they shine too brightly, but I
want to live together with them without averting my eyes.
